The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered a commencement address at Hillsdale College in Michigan. He praised the college for its commitment to freedom and its promotion of unchanging truths. Pence also discussed the current state of America, highlighting its growing economy and the restoration of its stature on the world stage. He emphasized the importance of faith in America and how it continues to hold a significant place in the lives of many Americans. Pence encouraged the graduating class to take their convictions and values into every aspect of their lives and to contribute to the renewal of the nation. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the class's ability to make America greater than ever before.